    "source_sections": {
      "references": "[Er50] Erd\\H{o}s, P., On integers of the form $2^k+p$ and some related problems. Summa Brasil. Math. (1950), 113-123.",
      "remarks": "Erd\\H{o}s \\cite{Er50} proved that there are infinitely many $n$ such that $f(n)\\gg \\log\\log n$.\n\nErd\\H{o}s could not even prove that there do not exist infinitely many integers $n$ such that for all $1< 2^k<n$ the number $n-2^k$ is prime - see [1142].\n\nThe sequence of values of $f(n)$ is A109925 on the OEIS.\n\nSee also [237]."
    },
